go_data.justification: DnaJC15 is described as an HSP70-stimulating cochaperone, indicating involvement in protein folding.
DnaJC15 is part of the TIM23-PAM system, which is essential for the import of precursor proteins into the mitochondrial matrix.
DnaJC15 is identified as an HSP70-stimulating cochaperone, implying it has cochaperone activity.
